Police said there were no signs of forced entry to the house which is currently being renovated. JOHANNESBURG - Police are still trying to find out who is responsible for a break-in at the house of National Police Commissioner Kehla Sitole's house in Mpumalanga. Two television sets were taken from the house by unidentified individuals. Police said there were no signs of forced entry to the house which is currently being renovated. Spokesperson Vishnu Naidoo said they were following several leads. “This was an opportunistic crime and we are exploring multiple possibilities.”